Exxon Flares Gases at Baton Rouge Plant After Pressure Rises

-- B y   T h e o   M u l l e n
-- 
2011-03-19T15:44:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-19/exxon-flares-gases-at-baton-rouge-plant-after-pressure-rises.html
  Exxon Mobil Corp. (XOM)  flared gases at
into the atmosphere at its  Baton Rouge  refinery after a process
upset that caused pressure to rise, the company said in a
filing.  A  report  filed with the National Response Center showed the
incident took place yesterday.  U.S. refineries must notify the National Response Center if
they release hazardous substances in excess of reportable
quantities, according to the Comprehensive Environmental
Response, Compensation and Liability Act, commonly known as
Superfund.  Baton Rouge is 81 miles (130 kilometers) northwest of New
Orleans.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theo Mullen at 
